FALSE DRAUGR REFERENCE
Frogs-5-Skyrim System — For GM Use Only
Recurring Enemy Type — First Appearance: Forelhost Laboratory (Session 11)


________________


SECTION 1: WHAT THEY ARE


FALSE DRAUGR — "ANTOINE'S BREAKERS"

Antoine of Forelhost built these as laboratory security. They are alchemical
constructs — copper-plated frames filled with pressurized VENITAS-saturated
fluid, animated by chemistry, not by death-energy or spiritual bonds. They
LOOK like Draugr. They are not Draugr. They are not undead. They are not
alive. They occupy a blind spot between every category the party knows.

Antoine studied Ulag the Breaker his entire life — the only siege engine he
ever observed up close. The False Draugr are crude working copies of Ulag's
method: pin, then shatter. They fight like a downscaled Breaker — slow,
relentless, built to hold a target still so something else can finish it.
They share his flaw: the brittle resonance that undoes his crystalline core
undoes them too.

They are not soldiers. They are lab equipment that fights.


DESIGN PRINCIPLE: THE FULL INVERSION

Every dimension of a regular Draugr has been deliberately inverted. A party
that walks in with the standard anti-undead playbook — fire, Turn Undead,
Detect Undead, sneak past — will have every assumption punished. The things
that work are the things the party does NOT usually reach for: invisibility,
cold, lightning, standing still, and pouring healing potions on the enemy.

This is Antoine's design philosophy made flesh: he builds things that look
familiar but work on entirely different principles. If the party treats them
like Draugr, the party loses.


