    original damage.

  Sonic / Thunder (Staggered 1 round)
    The resonance flaw copied from Ulag's crystalline core. Orion's War
    Horn lands here. A sustained note at the right frequency locks their
    joints and halts them for a full round.


DETECTION BLIND SPOT
  Detect Life:     No result. They are not alive.
  Detect Undead:   No result. They are not undead.
  Detect Magic:    Faint alchemical residue only — registers as ambient,
                   not as a creature or enchantment. Easily missed.
  Aura reading:    Nothing. No soul, no spiritual signature, no death-
                   energy. To magical senses they are furniture.

  A party relying on detection magic to scout will walk into these blind.
  This is intentional. Antoine built them to be invisible to every standard
  scan. The only way to know they are there is to see them with your eyes
  or feel them with your feet (once they are already moving).


TREMORSENSE (30 ft)
  False Draugr have no eyes and cannot see. They detect living things
  through vibration in the floor and air pressure changes — the copper
  plating acts as a resonance sensor.

  Invisibility:     Full effect. They cannot see you.
  Darkness:          Full effect. They cannot see.
  Conventional stealth (sneaking): DOES NOT WORK. Any creature moving
    within 30 feet on the same surface is automatically detected. They
    feel your weight, not your shadow. No Agility roll will help.
  Being motionless:  Undetectable. Stand perfectly still and they lose you.
  Being airborne:    Undetectable. Levitation, being carried, standing on
    furniture — anything that takes weight off the floor.

  TACTICAL IMPLICATION: against regular Draugr, you sneak past (Agility
  vs Guile). Against False Draugr, sneaking fails — but invisibility
  potions work, standing still works, and getting off the ground works.
  The solution set is completely different.


ALCHEMICAL REGENERATION
  At the start of each of its turns, a False Draugr regains 3 HP unless
  it took Cold or Lightning damage since its last turn.

  This is the inverse of Undying Loyalty:
    Draugr:       Easy to GET to 0 HP. Hard to KEEP them at 0.
                  The puzzle is finishing them (fire / skull crush).
    False Draugr: Hard to GET to 0 HP (they heal). Easy to keep at 0.
                  The puzzle is suppressing regen (cold / lightning)
                  and bursting them down.

  Without cold or lightning, a party hacking at them with swords is
  fighting uphill — 3 HP per round of passive healing on a 35 HP frame.
  With cold or lightning, the regen stops and damage sticks. The party
  MUST use their weaknesses to win efficiently.


DEATH SPLASH
  When reduced to 0 HP, the pressurized alchemical fluids rupture.
  All creatures within 5 feet take 3 chemical damage (VENITAS-saturated
  fluid, burns on contact).

  This creates a dilemma: melee them down and risk the splash, or use
  ranged cold/lightning to finish them safely from a distance.

  This is the inverse of the Draugr death-threat:
    Draugr death:       Threatens you AFTER dying (reassembly).
    False Draugr death: Threatens you DURING dying (splash).


VITALIS VULNERABILITY
  They are VENITAS-saturated constructs. VITALIS is the opposition Essence.

  A healing potion poured directly onto a False Draugr (Major Action,
  must be adjacent) deals damage equal to the potion's HP value and
  ignores DR:
    Minor Healing Potion:     4 damage (ignores DR)
    Healing Potion:           8 damage (ignores DR)
    Plentiful Healing Potion: 12 damage (ignores DR)

  The VITALIS causes an opposition reaction in the animation medium —
  the fluid curdles, the joints seize, the construct partially collapses.

  This is the reward for a player who has read the Doctrine of Essences
  and thinks with the alchemy system. It is also thematically perfect:
  Antoine's Scourge is designed so healing feeds the plague. His constructs
  have the same principle in reverse — healing kills them.

  GM NOTE: Do not hint at this. The player must reason to it from the
  alchemy rules. If they do, celebrate it — this is a system mastery
  reward of the highest order.


