SECTION 5: BEHAVIOR


PROGRAMMED ROUTINES (NO ADAPTATION)

  False Draugr do not think. They execute behavioral scripts:

  1. Detect vibration → move toward source.
  2. Reach target → Restraining Grapple (always attempts grapple first).
  3. Target restrained → Breaker's Blow (the pin-then-shatter sequence).
  4. Target not restrained → Alchemical Blade (soften with Numbness,
     then attempt grapple again next turn).
  5. Multiple targets → always prioritize the NEAREST. Never switch
     targets mid-routine.

  They do not flank. They do not coordinate. They do not adapt to what
  the party is doing. They execute the script every round, identically.

  EXPLOITING THE SCRIPT: A player who spends a round observing a specific
  Breaker (forgoing their own action to watch) can predict exactly what
  it will do next. Mechanically: they gain Advantage on their next action
  against that Breaker. This rewards patience — but in the Forelhost
  encounter, the 5-minute IRL timer creates tension against spending a
  turn watching instead of acting.


CONTAINMENT BEHAVIOR

  They fight to CONTAIN, not kill. Their entire role is to hold targets
  in place for the sterilization field / cage trap. In the Forelhost
  encounter specifically:
    - They prioritize anyone approaching the containment cage.
    - They grapple and pin anyone attempting to free the caged PC.
    - They do not pursue outside the laboratory.
    - They do not pursue at all — if a target leaves their 30-foot
      tremorsense range, they return to patrol.

  For recurring encounters outside Forelhost:
    They guard whatever Antoine (or whoever controls them) has told them
    to guard. They do not pursue beyond their designated zone. They do
    not adapt their patrol routes. They are guard dogs with no initiative.


SILENCE

  They make no vocalizations. No moans. No chants. No breath.

  What the party hears:
    - The hiss of pressurized steam venting from shoulder valves.
    - The click-click-click of copper joints articulating.
    - The scrape of copper-plated feet on stone.
    - A low, rhythmic thrumming — the alchemical fluids circulating
      inside the frame — audible only in close proximity.

  This is one of their most unsettling qualities. Draugr ANNOUNCE
  themselves with moans and chanting. False Draugr are wrong precisely
  because they are quiet. The silence tells the party that these are
  not the dead. These are something else.


