SECTION 7: RECURRING USE NOTES


WHERE THEY APPEAR

  First: Forelhost Laboratory (Session 11, Riften arc).
         Lab security for Antoine's containment trap.

  Future: Anywhere Antoine has had time to set up a workspace.
          Anywhere the Dragon Cult's Forelhost line has operated.
          Potentially mass-produced if Antoine acquires the resources
          and the time — a squad of these guarding a chokepoint is a
          very different encounter than six in an open lab.


SCALING FOR FUTURE ENCOUNTERS

  The base stat block is Expert-tier. For recurring use at higher party
  tiers, scale as follows:

  Advanced Breaker (party at Adept tier):
    HP 45. DR 6. Regen 4/turn. Alchemical Blade 8 damage.
    Numbness becomes -3 Agility. Breaker's Blow 12 damage.
    Same weaknesses, same behavioral script. More durable, more punishing.

  Siege Breaker (party at Master tier):
    HP 60. DR 8. Regen 5/turn. Alchemical Blade 10 damage.
    Add: Pressurized Spray (recharge, 15ft cone, 6 chemical damage,
    Standard Might or Blinded 1 round — VENITAS fluid sprayed from
    chest vents). Breaker's Blow 15 damage.
    This is the version Antoine builds when he is no longer improvising.

  The behavioral script does NOT scale. They never get smarter. They get
  tougher and more punishing, but the same observational exploit works
  at every tier. The party that learned the trick at Expert tier carries
  that knowledge forward. That is the reward for paying attention.


NARRATIVE FUNCTION

  False Draugr are Antoine's signature — the way a player recognizes his
  work. When the party enters a space and finds copper-plated silent
  things standing in alcoves, they know Antoine has been here. They know
  what to expect (the script, the weaknesses, the containment role) and
  they know what they are walking into.

  They are also the party's proof that Antoine builds weapons by copying
  things he has studied. He studied Ulag — he built the Breakers. If the
  party ever wonders what else Antoine could build, the answer is: copies
  of anything he has had time to study. This is his method. He observes,
  he replicates, he improves. The Breakers are the simplest expression
  of it. What comes next will be worse.


