SECTION 8: OPEN QUESTIONS (TO SETTLE IN FUTURE SESSIONS)


  1. Can the party salvage a destroyed Breaker for parts?
     The copper plating is valuable. The alchemical fluid residue could be
     studied. A character with alchemy knowledge might reverse-engineer
     the animation medium. Is this a loot opportunity or a narrative one?

  2. Can the party reprogram a Breaker?
     They run on behavioral scripts. If someone understood the scripting
     mechanism, could they redirect one? This is probably Master-tier
     alchemy or enchantment if it is possible at all.

  3. Does Antoine improve them between encounters?
     If the party fights Breakers and wins, does Antoine learn from the
     loss and adjust? His design philosophy suggests yes — he iterates.
     But the behavioral script is a fundamental limitation of the
     construct type. He can make them tougher but not smarter. That gap
     is his blind spot — he copies Ulag's strength but not Ulag's
     rudimentary cunning.

  4. Are there other construct types?
     Antoine studied Ulag — the Breakers copy Ulag. If Antoine studies
     other things (a mage, an animal, a different combat style), could
     he build constructs that copy THOSE? Different stat profiles,
     different scripts, same core weaknesses? This opens a design space
     for future encounters.

  5. What happens to Breakers outside the death ward?
     Inside Forelhost, the sterile environment preserves them indefinitely.
     Outside, exposed to weather and biological contamination, do they
     degrade over time? Are they field-deployable or lab-only? This has
     implications for where the party might encounter them.


